1
00:00:31,018 --> 00:00:32,520
<i>This is crazy.</i>

2
00:00:32,603 --> 00:00:35,565
<i>But it was so good.</i>

3
00:00:38,192 --> 00:00:40,069
I want to keep sleeping like this.

4
00:00:40,653 --> 00:00:41,696
Me too.

5
00:00:43,531 --> 00:00:45,074
Should we skip school?

6
00:01:29,577 --> 00:01:32,538
<i>At least if I was drunk,
I could have used that as an excuse.</i>

7
00:01:37,668 --> 00:01:42,340
EPISODE 4: I KNOW IT ISN'T LOVE.
NEVERTHELESS,

8
00:01:49,764 --> 00:01:52,224
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

9
00:01:52,308 --> 00:01:54,602
Where's the hair dryer?

10
00:01:55,186 --> 00:01:57,480
-Darn it.
-Let's talk.

11
00:01:59,315 --> 00:02:01,484
Hey, put your clothes on!

12
00:02:05,196 --> 00:02:07,740
I must have alcohol-related dementia.

13
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,743
I don't remember what happened yesterday.

14
00:02:11,285 --> 00:02:13,412
-So--
-It was a mistake?

15
00:02:13,496 --> 00:02:14,622
What?

16
00:02:18,834 --> 00:02:22,296
Yes. Honestly, we both
made a mistake while drunk, right?

17
00:02:23,422 --> 00:02:26,217
So there's nothing to change between us.

18
00:02:27,051 --> 00:02:28,135
Don't you think?

19
00:02:28,636 --> 00:02:29,720
I'm leaving.

20
00:02:30,304 --> 00:02:33,516
Hey! Wait!

21
00:02:38,229 --> 00:02:41,148
Darn it! I must have lost my mind!

22
00:02:41,899 --> 00:02:44,193
Why did it have to be him?

23
00:02:54,203 --> 00:02:55,454
Is that mine?

24
00:02:56,247 --> 00:02:59,041
Yes. I washed it.

25
00:03:00,751 --> 00:03:02,086
It's fine, you can have it.

26
00:03:03,295 --> 00:03:04,839
Or just throw it away.

27
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,342
Right.
I'm going to have breakfast outside.

28
00:03:09,009 --> 00:03:10,177
Outside?

29
00:03:10,261 --> 00:03:11,470
By myself.

30
00:03:12,638 --> 00:03:15,850
Oh, right. I get it.

31
00:03:16,517 --> 00:03:18,561
I should get some more sleep.

32
00:03:19,228 --> 00:03:20,479
Go ahead.

33
00:03:25,192 --> 00:03:26,777
I want to keep seeing you.

34
00:03:28,821 --> 00:03:29,697
What about you?

35
00:03:30,281 --> 00:03:31,907
<i>This is it.</i>

36
00:03:31,991 --> 00:03:33,284
What do you mean?

37
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:34,660
Should we meet up sometimes?

38
00:03:35,244 --> 00:03:38,247
<i>So he's asking if I want to meet up</i>

39
00:03:38,873 --> 00:03:41,917
<i>and sleep with him sometimes</i>

40
00:03:42,001 --> 00:03:43,669
<i>without dating?</i>

41
00:03:44,628 --> 00:03:45,963
I'm not sure.

42
00:03:47,173 --> 00:03:48,507
Think about it and tell me.

43
00:03:49,216 --> 00:03:53,179
I'll be off. Go to the hospital
if you're not feeling well. Okay?

44
00:03:54,054 --> 00:03:55,264
Okay.

45
00:04:19,997 --> 00:04:21,290
Park Jae-eon?

46
00:04:37,723 --> 00:04:40,684
-It wasn't a mistake for me.
-What?

47
00:04:40,768 --> 00:04:43,938
And things won't be the same
for me, either.

48
00:04:44,021 --> 00:04:46,774
So I don't think I can pretend
it didn't happen.

49
00:04:52,738 --> 00:04:54,073
What if you don't?

50
00:04:54,156 --> 00:04:58,035
I don't think I can stay friends
with you now.

51
00:04:58,118 --> 00:04:59,495
Then what?

52
00:05:01,539 --> 00:05:03,916
-You don't mean…
-Be my girlfriend.

53
00:05:10,256 --> 00:05:13,300
Hey! You…

54
00:05:15,261 --> 00:05:19,682
You want to date because we slept
together once? You're overreacting.

55
00:05:19,765 --> 00:05:20,975
Do you like me?

56
00:05:24,645 --> 00:05:27,189
See? You can't answer that.

57
00:05:27,273 --> 00:05:30,693
Plus, I really don't want to date
within such a small department.

58
00:05:30,776 --> 00:05:32,236
Rumors will spread so quickly.

59
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:33,988
It's going to be really irritating.

60
00:05:38,617 --> 00:05:39,702
All right.

61
00:05:40,828 --> 00:05:44,164
I understand how you feel,
so I'll take care of my own feelings.

62
00:05:44,748 --> 00:05:48,085
What do you mean? Hey!

63
00:05:52,506 --> 00:05:55,384
The guy Sol brought over last night.
Was he her boyfriend?

64
00:05:56,468 --> 00:05:57,553
I don't know.

65
00:05:58,429 --> 00:06:00,514
Jeez!

66
00:06:01,015 --> 00:06:03,225
You're the only one who'd know!

67
00:06:03,309 --> 00:06:05,477
Who is he? Is it…

68
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,065
Is it serious?

69
00:06:10,816 --> 00:06:12,985
Ask her yourself.

70
00:06:13,068 --> 00:06:15,946
I don't care who she dates.

71
00:06:16,030 --> 00:06:17,406
This is so annoying.

72
00:06:17,948 --> 00:06:19,992
What? Did you two fight?

73
00:06:22,161 --> 00:06:25,497
Right. You didn't know about
Sol leaving as an exchange student too.

74
00:06:25,998 --> 00:06:29,084
We didn't fight. That's just
the extent of our relationship.

75
00:06:30,085 --> 00:06:31,128
I'm going.

76
00:06:45,142 --> 00:06:46,268
Seo Ji-wan.

77
00:06:47,102 --> 00:06:49,813
Ji-wan. Ji-wan!

78
00:06:50,689 --> 00:06:52,107
Let me talk to you.

79
00:06:54,985 --> 00:06:57,488
Fine. Talk.
What do you want to talk about first?

80
00:06:57,571 --> 00:07:00,366
Going abroad? Or your boyfriend?

81
00:07:01,116 --> 00:07:02,660
Everyone knew except me.

82
00:07:02,743 --> 00:07:04,370
I was going to tell you.

83
00:07:04,453 --> 00:07:06,872
Right. When were you going to tell me?

84
00:07:06,956 --> 00:07:09,625
The day before you left?
The day before you got married?

85
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:12,503
What's with you?
You said you don't care who I date.

86
00:07:12,586 --> 00:07:14,088
Right. I don't.

87
00:07:14,171 --> 00:07:16,757
I'm just angry because
you're leaving me out like this.

88
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:19,760
-When did I leave you out--
-You've always done this.

89
00:07:19,843 --> 00:07:23,597
You never tell me important things
about yourself. You know that?

90
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,059
Like what?

91
00:07:40,614 --> 00:07:44,159
I guess this really is the extent
of our relationship.

92
00:08:09,184 --> 00:08:10,436
Thanks.

93
00:08:12,312 --> 00:08:13,647
What's your next class?

94
00:08:14,565 --> 00:08:17,234
Human Anatomy. It's so hard.

95
00:08:18,235 --> 00:08:19,903
I got an A in that class.

96
00:08:19,987 --> 00:08:21,321
-Really?
-Yes.

97
00:08:21,405 --> 00:08:24,283
-Then help me study.
-What will you do for me, then?

98
00:08:29,038 --> 00:08:30,456
What should I do for you?

99
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:33,959
Jeez…

100
00:08:37,963 --> 00:08:40,924
By the way…

101
00:08:42,885 --> 00:08:44,011
Well…

102
00:08:45,137 --> 00:08:49,349
I don't want anyone to know about us.

103
00:08:51,685 --> 00:08:53,520
All right.

104
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:56,190
-Okay.
-Okay.

105
00:08:57,524 --> 00:08:59,318
And…

106
00:09:00,152 --> 00:09:01,528
Well…

107
00:09:02,112 --> 00:09:03,447
You don't…

108
00:09:05,282 --> 00:09:09,495
have any diseases or anything, do you?

109
00:09:12,831 --> 00:09:13,791
Do you?

110
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,213
Don't laugh! I'm serious.

111
00:09:20,589 --> 00:09:22,508
I don't, so don't worry.

112
00:09:24,885 --> 00:09:26,136
Okay.

113
00:09:27,679 --> 00:09:29,264
Do you have time later?

114
00:09:31,266 --> 00:09:33,894
Yes, I have some time.

115
00:09:33,977 --> 00:09:36,396
No, should we meet on Saturday?

116
00:09:37,898 --> 00:09:39,691
You need to rest the next day, right?

117
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:44,780
No. It's totally fine.

118
00:10:19,022 --> 00:10:22,317
<i>Why did I do that? I acted so impulsively.</i>

119
00:10:23,986 --> 00:10:25,487
I must've lost my mind.

120
00:10:31,118 --> 00:10:33,245
I should just tell him not to come.

121
00:10:49,761 --> 00:10:51,680
-Come in.
-Hey.

122
00:10:58,353 --> 00:10:59,605
What's with the alcohol?

123
00:11:01,023 --> 00:11:02,941
It'll be nice to drink together.

124
00:11:03,025 --> 00:11:04,318
It'll be fun.

125
00:11:05,444 --> 00:11:07,738
Oh, I drank some already.

126
00:11:07,821 --> 00:11:10,490
<i>I couldn't do this sober.</i>

127
00:11:12,159 --> 00:11:13,827
This is cheating.

128
00:11:14,411 --> 00:11:15,287
What do you mean?

129
00:11:16,830 --> 00:11:19,041
We didn't decide on anything.

130
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:22,210
Decide what?

131
00:11:22,294 --> 00:11:25,756
Weren't we going to study
Human Anatomy together?

132
00:11:27,341 --> 00:11:28,926
Oh, right.

133
00:11:30,302 --> 00:11:31,845
Right. Human Anatomy.

134
00:11:34,097 --> 00:11:36,016
Yes. We should study.

135
00:11:41,605 --> 00:11:43,023
Stop laughing.

136
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:46,318
I have a gift for you.

137
00:11:56,578 --> 00:11:59,331
<i>Jae-eon is too smooth with everything.</i>

138
00:11:59,831 --> 00:12:03,627
<i>It's like everything
comes naturally to him.</i>

139
00:12:04,211 --> 00:12:05,712
All done.

140
00:12:09,841 --> 00:12:10,801
Do you like it?

141
00:12:12,386 --> 00:12:13,512
Yes.

142
00:12:15,764 --> 00:12:16,974
It's pretty.

143
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:21,228
It'll be prettier
with the sunlight in the morning.

144
00:12:34,366 --> 00:12:36,535
<i>Like this was always
going to happen between us.</i>

145
00:12:41,873 --> 00:12:43,458
You got me again.

146
00:12:49,548 --> 00:12:50,757
Hang on.

147
00:12:55,971 --> 00:12:57,556
PARK JAE-EON

148
00:13:00,183 --> 00:13:01,560
You saved my number.

149
00:13:08,191 --> 00:13:09,860
<i>I can stop this right now.</i>

150
00:13:11,695 --> 00:13:15,657
<i>Because there are so many reasons
why I shouldn't do this.</i>

151
00:13:20,328 --> 00:13:21,621
<i>But…</i>

152
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:47,230
You know, you have a mole here.

153
00:13:48,273 --> 00:13:49,107
Where?

154
00:13:50,108 --> 00:13:51,109
Here.

155
00:13:54,946 --> 00:13:56,156
I didn't know.

156
00:14:01,036 --> 00:14:03,997
You look even more pretty today.

157
00:14:04,081 --> 00:14:06,875
<i>I'm still attracted to him,
even at this moment.</i>

158
00:14:08,919 --> 00:14:10,420
<i>Like crazy.</i>

159
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:33,610
<i>That one simple reason</i>

160
00:14:35,028 --> 00:14:37,489
<i>buries all my concerns again.</i>

161
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:46,706
Didn't it hurt when you got that tattoo
behind your neck?

162
00:14:49,793 --> 00:14:51,420
Of course, it hurt.

163
00:14:52,587 --> 00:14:54,214
I almost died.

164
00:14:56,174 --> 00:14:57,843
I thought of quitting in the middle.

165
00:15:02,264 --> 00:15:04,057
I'm going to get another one soon.

166
00:15:05,225 --> 00:15:06,351
Where?

167
00:15:10,689 --> 00:15:12,065
Around here.

168
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:16,445
Another butterfly?

169
00:15:16,528 --> 00:15:17,571
Yes.

170
00:15:19,239 --> 00:15:22,909
A butterfly with lots of black spots
on its wings.

171
00:15:22,993 --> 00:15:24,369
The name's pretty difficult.

172
00:15:25,078 --> 00:15:28,623
Taiwanese black-star hairstreak butterfly.

173
00:15:31,042 --> 00:15:32,169
Taiwan…

174
00:15:33,378 --> 00:15:34,838
That's a really long name.

175
00:15:38,675 --> 00:15:41,011
They eat flowers instead of leaves

176
00:15:41,094 --> 00:15:43,638
when they're caterpillars.

177
00:15:44,764 --> 00:15:46,057
It's unique, right?

178
00:15:47,934 --> 00:15:48,935
Yes.

179
00:15:49,936 --> 00:15:53,315
<i>Since that day, a lot of things
have changed between us.</i>

180
00:15:54,107 --> 00:15:57,360
<i>And Jae-eon slowly seeped into my life.</i>

181
00:16:02,741 --> 00:16:04,117
Get washed.

182
00:16:12,876 --> 00:16:14,878
I'm starting work
at the department office.

183
00:16:14,961 --> 00:16:17,881
You decided to do that? Aren't you busy?

184
00:16:17,964 --> 00:16:20,926
I won't work that long. Just for a while.

185
00:16:24,387 --> 00:16:25,514
It's because of you.

186
00:16:28,892 --> 00:16:29,935
Why?

187
00:16:31,895 --> 00:16:33,230
Come visit often.

188
00:16:34,356 --> 00:16:36,399
-Why would I?
-What?

189
00:16:38,193 --> 00:16:39,569
Come visit me.

190
00:16:41,321 --> 00:16:43,031
All right?

191
00:16:43,114 --> 00:16:44,241
Why would I?

192
00:16:46,493 --> 00:16:47,994
Okay, I will.

193
00:16:54,459 --> 00:16:57,879
Jae-eon, where's that suncatcher
you made last time?

194
00:16:57,963 --> 00:16:59,381
The butterfly-shaped one.

195
00:16:59,881 --> 00:17:01,049
Oh, that?

196
00:17:02,259 --> 00:17:03,510
I gifted it to someone.

197
00:17:03,593 --> 00:17:07,055
That's too bad. I wanted to see it
when it was finished.

198
00:17:07,138 --> 00:17:10,058
-Can you tell us how to make it?
-Tell us!

199
00:17:10,141 --> 00:17:12,394
Learn that from
the Ceramics and Glass students.

200
00:17:12,477 --> 00:17:14,437
Jae-eon is mine now.

201
00:17:15,814 --> 00:17:17,607
What are you talking about?

202
00:17:17,691 --> 00:17:19,693
Darn it! You're so noisy.

203
00:17:20,443 --> 00:17:23,738
If you're done, please just leave.

204
00:17:24,489 --> 00:17:27,075
-Guys, get out.
-Okay.

205
00:17:27,158 --> 00:17:29,160
-Bye.
-Bye.

206
00:17:32,205 --> 00:17:35,333
I heard he doesn't date,
but I guess he has a girlfriend.

207
00:17:35,417 --> 00:17:37,711
I wonder who it is.
She must be really pretty.

208
00:17:54,853 --> 00:17:56,896
-It's raining a lot.
-It is.

209
00:18:06,281 --> 00:18:08,742
-Don't do it.
-I have to do this!

210
00:18:08,825 --> 00:18:11,077
Stop working. Let's just sleep.

211
00:18:11,620 --> 00:18:12,954
-Already?
-Yes.

212
00:18:14,539 --> 00:18:16,916
-Already?
-Yes. I'm sleepy.

213
00:18:25,425 --> 00:18:29,679
<i>Our relationship only exists
at night, but…</i>

214
00:18:31,222 --> 00:18:32,932
Are you washing the dishes?

215
00:18:33,016 --> 00:18:36,186
Yes. It seems like you don't do the dishes
when I'm coming.

216
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:38,021
You caught me.

217
00:18:38,688 --> 00:18:40,899
I think you're pretty good at housework.

218
00:18:41,775 --> 00:18:43,485
Will you do the laundry too?

219
00:18:44,277 --> 00:18:46,237
-Should I?
-Yes.

220
00:18:46,321 --> 00:18:50,408
-Then let's do it together.
-No. I don't want to do it.

221
00:18:50,492 --> 00:18:54,079
<i>It sometimes felt like we were lovers.</i>

222
00:18:54,788 --> 00:18:56,373
What's your goal today?

223
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:01,503
Really? Can you do it?

224
00:19:03,588 --> 00:19:05,048
Don't strain yourself.

225
00:19:11,054 --> 00:19:12,055
What was that?

226
00:19:14,265 --> 00:19:17,602
My tongue gets numb when I eat this.

227
00:19:18,395 --> 00:19:19,604
So I kissed you first.

228
00:19:19,688 --> 00:19:22,774
<i>Jae-eon is still a mystery to me.</i>

229
00:19:22,857 --> 00:19:24,234
What are you on about?

230
00:19:24,317 --> 00:19:25,527
-Let's eat.
-Okay.

231
00:19:27,195 --> 00:19:28,363
Here.

232
00:19:32,659 --> 00:19:36,329
You said your tongue gets numb.
This is good, though.

233
00:19:36,830 --> 00:19:37,956
-Really?
-Yes.

234
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:45,255
Just eat.

235
00:19:50,510 --> 00:19:52,679
-It's good, right?
-Yes. It's tastier today.

236
00:20:14,826 --> 00:20:18,079
<i>I can't tell if he's warm or cold,</i>

237
00:20:18,955 --> 00:20:21,499
<i>serious or joking.</i>

238
00:20:36,306 --> 00:20:38,099
Are you done with assignments?

239
00:20:38,725 --> 00:20:39,934
No.

240
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,687
Go sleep at your house.

241
00:20:46,191 --> 00:20:47,817
I can't just leave.

242
00:21:01,414 --> 00:21:04,334
<i>My anxiety about Jae-eon
hasn't disappeared, but…</i>

243
00:21:15,470 --> 00:21:17,555
<i>We're much more compatible than I thought.</i>

244
00:21:23,561 --> 00:21:25,605
So the transverse arch

245
00:21:25,688 --> 00:21:27,690
can be seen the best from the front.

246
00:21:27,774 --> 00:21:30,902
I see. You're right.

247
00:21:31,778 --> 00:21:34,489
This is the transverse arch?

248
00:21:35,073 --> 00:21:36,032
Yes.

249
00:21:36,783 --> 00:21:39,452
And this is the medial longitudinal arch.

250
00:21:40,495 --> 00:21:43,331
-Yes.
-This is the lateral longitudinal arch.

251
00:21:44,374 --> 00:21:45,291
Correct.

252
00:21:47,877 --> 00:21:50,380
-What about this?
-Stop. It tickles.

253
00:21:50,463 --> 00:21:51,673
Stop.

254
00:21:51,756 --> 00:21:53,675
I'm studying right now.

255
00:21:55,051 --> 00:21:56,094
What about this?

256
00:21:56,177 --> 00:21:58,137
Hey, it tickles.

257
00:22:05,812 --> 00:22:07,772
<i>And I enjoy</i>

258
00:22:08,773 --> 00:22:10,233
<i>spending nights with him.</i>

259
00:22:19,158 --> 00:22:20,451
Thank you.

260
00:22:23,371 --> 00:22:24,872
-It looks delicious.
-I want corn.

261
00:22:24,956 --> 00:22:26,291
I thought you were on a diet.

262
00:22:26,374 --> 00:22:29,627
-That's why I'm only eating the shrimp.
-Oh, is that right?

263
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:35,425
Are you dating someone these days?

264
00:22:36,009 --> 00:22:37,051
Me?

265
00:22:39,721 --> 00:22:41,264
No. Why?

266
00:22:41,347 --> 00:22:45,143
You just seem to be in a good mood
these days.

267
