happiness so I can feel proud?

526
00:43:33,932 --> 00:43:37,018
All right. Thank you!

527
00:43:37,102 --> 00:43:38,436
Wear it tomorrow, okay?

528
00:43:39,146 --> 00:43:40,355
Okay.

529
00:43:41,314 --> 00:43:44,568
But weren't you going to the exhibit?
It's the last day today.

530
00:43:46,361 --> 00:43:48,780
How could I think about that right now?

531
00:43:49,322 --> 00:43:51,199
<i>He's making me get my hopes up again.</i>

532
00:43:51,283 --> 00:43:52,284
Then…

533
00:43:53,285 --> 00:43:56,329
You got me a gift,
so let me buy you a meal.

534
00:43:56,955 --> 00:43:58,331
Well…

535
00:44:00,250 --> 00:44:01,877
Oh, do you have plans?

536
00:44:02,544 --> 00:44:03,628
Then--

537
00:44:03,712 --> 00:44:05,881
No. It's your birthday, so…

538
00:44:08,049 --> 00:44:10,051
INSTANT SEAWEED SOUP

539
00:44:14,306 --> 00:44:16,516
<i>I thought it was the worst birthday ever.</i>

540
00:44:17,392 --> 00:44:20,353
<i>But I guess life is full of variables.</i>

541
00:44:22,022 --> 00:44:23,982
Hang on. I'll make this right away.

542
00:44:28,904 --> 00:44:30,864
You're talking
as if you're really cooking.

543
00:44:32,073 --> 00:44:33,783
It's the heart that matters.

544
00:44:35,201 --> 00:44:38,496
It's been a while since I had
seaweed soup for my birthday.

545
00:44:40,832 --> 00:44:42,208
Really?

546
00:44:42,918 --> 00:44:45,587
I thought everyone had it except for me.

547
00:44:46,379 --> 00:44:47,547
I feel comforted now.

548
00:44:58,767 --> 00:44:59,768
What?

549
00:44:59,851 --> 00:45:02,020
You've never told me
something like that before.

550
00:45:03,730 --> 00:45:05,482
You don't talk much about yourself.

551
00:45:07,067 --> 00:45:08,401
Well…

552
00:45:12,989 --> 00:45:16,576
That's because
you know me so well already.

553
00:45:19,955 --> 00:45:21,706
I don't know anything about you.

554
00:45:28,421 --> 00:45:29,589
I really don't.

555
00:45:30,715 --> 00:45:32,509
You're still such a mystery to me.

556
00:45:40,976 --> 00:45:43,645
Stop fooling around
and finish making this.

557
00:45:44,229 --> 00:45:45,438
Not that.

558
00:45:47,941 --> 00:45:49,150
Then what?

559
00:46:52,714 --> 00:46:56,217
<i>Why can't you be my boyfriend?</i>

560
00:47:00,180 --> 00:47:02,807
So when are you going to make me
the seaweed soup?

561
00:47:05,185 --> 00:47:06,519
I'll make it now.

562
00:47:07,353 --> 00:47:09,105
Why aren't you getting up, then?

563
00:47:09,898 --> 00:47:12,067
I have no energy. Five more minutes.

564
00:47:25,538 --> 00:47:27,332
SEOL-A

565
00:47:30,543 --> 00:47:31,503
Let me take a call.

566
00:47:32,796 --> 00:47:34,089
Hang on.

567
00:47:39,177 --> 00:47:41,346
Should we have a drink first?

568
00:47:41,429 --> 00:47:44,015
Or go right away?

569
00:47:44,099 --> 00:47:46,518
Well, whatever you prefer.

570
00:47:52,774 --> 00:47:54,526
Let's drink here.

571
00:47:59,322 --> 00:48:00,698
What's your ideal type?

572
00:48:00,782 --> 00:48:01,991
-Me?
-Yes.

573
00:48:06,287 --> 00:48:07,247
Are you okay?

574
00:48:09,707 --> 00:48:11,292
Yes. I'm okay.

575
00:48:20,093 --> 00:48:24,013
This place is actually pretty lame.

576
00:48:27,100 --> 00:48:28,726
-Let's drink somewhere else.
-What?

577
00:48:28,810 --> 00:48:30,854
-Let's go.
-Somewhere else?

578
00:48:42,323 --> 00:48:43,908
Do you know her?

579
00:48:44,534 --> 00:48:46,202
No, I don't.

580
00:48:46,286 --> 00:48:48,621
Excuse me. Can I have some ice water?

581
00:48:52,959 --> 00:48:55,837
Sorry. Something urgent came up
with a friend.

582
00:48:57,714 --> 00:48:59,632
Okay. You should go, then.

583
00:49:00,216 --> 00:49:04,262
Make sure to eat.
And don't ignore your mom.

584
00:49:06,848 --> 00:49:08,016
I'll get going.

585
00:49:09,058 --> 00:49:10,226
Okay.

586
00:49:41,382 --> 00:49:42,842
I'm hungry.

587
00:50:41,359 --> 00:50:42,777
Do-hyeok…

588
00:50:51,119 --> 00:50:52,495
Come in.

589
00:50:58,126 --> 00:51:00,211
Sorry. You're closed, right? I…

590
00:51:00,295 --> 00:51:01,421
We're not.

591
00:51:08,594 --> 00:51:11,806
What? You have 3,000 subscribers?

592
00:51:12,390 --> 00:51:13,933
You started only three months ago.

593
00:51:14,017 --> 00:51:15,643
You have so many views.

594
00:51:15,727 --> 00:51:17,687
Do you edit the videos yourself?

595
00:51:18,438 --> 00:51:19,647
Yes.

596
00:51:21,524 --> 00:51:23,234
GRANDSON OF A NOODLE SHOP OWNER

597
00:51:23,318 --> 00:51:25,570
I saw this before.

598
00:51:26,446 --> 00:51:29,032
The channel name reminded me of you.

599
00:51:29,115 --> 00:51:30,616
You thought about me?

600
00:51:31,200 --> 00:51:32,452
Of course.

601
00:51:34,329 --> 00:51:36,789
I can't believe it really was you.

602
00:51:36,873 --> 00:51:38,333
And a culinary arts major?

603
00:51:39,500 --> 00:51:43,129
The Yang Do-hyeok I know

604
00:51:43,212 --> 00:51:45,923
always played with food.

605
00:51:49,844 --> 00:51:51,512
I knew you'd major in art, though.

606
00:51:52,430 --> 00:51:54,349
You were always good at drawing.

607
00:51:56,642 --> 00:51:58,019
Well…

608
00:51:59,979 --> 00:52:01,189
Not that good.

609
00:52:01,731 --> 00:52:03,483
I just liked it.

610
00:52:07,653 --> 00:52:09,572
Your videos are really good.

611
00:52:13,743 --> 00:52:14,744
Here you go.

612
00:52:19,832 --> 00:52:22,168
Weren't you making noodles for me?

613
00:52:22,794 --> 00:52:23,878
Next time.

614
00:52:24,629 --> 00:52:26,756
Isn't it your birthday today?

615
00:52:28,007 --> 00:52:29,467
You're right.

616
00:52:33,262 --> 00:52:35,932
You have a good memory.
You remembered my birthday?

617
00:52:36,557 --> 00:52:37,642
Of course, I…

618
00:52:41,521 --> 00:52:43,606
I have a good memory.

619
00:52:44,190 --> 00:52:45,108
Right.

620
00:52:45,775 --> 00:52:48,027
-Do you still like chocolate?
-Yes.

621
00:52:50,530 --> 00:52:52,240
Did you make this yourself, too?

622
00:52:53,032 --> 00:52:55,076
-Yes.
-You're so skilled.

623
00:52:55,159 --> 00:52:56,411
It looks delicious.

624
00:53:01,499 --> 00:53:02,500
What?

625
00:53:04,961 --> 00:53:06,170
Make a wish.

626
00:53:07,296 --> 00:53:08,673
A wish?

627
00:53:09,590 --> 00:53:10,842
All right.

628
00:53:30,194 --> 00:53:31,279
Happy birthday, Na-bi.

629
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:35,491
Thank you. I can't believe
I'm with you like this on my birthday.

630
00:53:35,575 --> 00:53:37,493
Life is full of surprises.

631
00:53:38,077 --> 00:53:40,997
I know.
I never imagined this would happen.

632
00:53:43,833 --> 00:53:45,460
-It's so good.
-Really?

633
00:53:45,543 --> 00:53:47,128
-Yes!
-That's a relief.

634
00:53:47,712 --> 00:53:49,630
I felt this last time,

635
00:53:49,714 --> 00:53:52,508
but it's not awkward
even when we haven't met for a long time.

636
00:53:53,009 --> 00:53:55,261
Maybe since we're childhood friends.

637
00:53:55,344 --> 00:53:56,637
Do you think so?

638
00:53:56,721 --> 00:53:59,015
What's that response? Do you feel awkward?

639
00:54:00,433 --> 00:54:02,727
I feel kind of nervous.

640
00:54:08,774 --> 00:54:12,320
Remember when we had a birthday party
at the beach?

641
00:54:12,403 --> 00:54:13,654
Yes. Right.

642
00:54:14,947 --> 00:54:15,948
Of course I remember.

643
00:54:16,699 --> 00:54:19,410
We set up a tent and made <i>ramyeon</i>.

644
00:54:19,494 --> 00:54:22,121
Right. And we played with fireworks.

645
00:54:22,872 --> 00:54:24,123
Right.

646
00:54:24,207 --> 00:54:25,917
It was so fun.

647
00:54:27,835 --> 00:54:29,378
I want to go back to that moment.

648
00:55:08,501 --> 00:55:09,752
Do you like your gift?

649
00:55:11,379 --> 00:55:14,006
I've never been forced to receive
a gift like this.

650
00:55:14,590 --> 00:55:16,133
Wear it tomorrow, okay?

651
00:55:44,870 --> 00:55:46,998
-Hello?
-<i>Are you at school?</i>

652
00:55:47,081 --> 00:55:47,999
Yes. Why?

653
00:55:48,082 --> 00:55:51,002
I'm on my way. I'll be there soon.

654
00:55:51,836 --> 00:55:53,254
Me too.

655
00:56:10,229 --> 00:56:11,606
It looks good on you.

656
00:56:15,484 --> 00:56:17,278
Because you bought it?

657
00:56:17,361 --> 00:56:19,864
Well, the model is pretty.

658
00:56:22,325 --> 00:56:23,409
You're right.

659
00:56:25,578 --> 00:56:27,413
Right, I made up with my mom.

660
00:56:27,496 --> 00:56:29,457
Well, it was more like

661
00:56:29,540 --> 00:56:31,834
I just listened to her talk and hung up.

662
00:56:33,586 --> 00:56:34,795
Good job.

663
00:56:37,256 --> 00:56:40,259
What about you?
You went to see your friend.

664
00:56:41,844 --> 00:56:42,720
Right.

665
00:56:44,555 --> 00:56:45,681
It wasn't anything good.

666
00:56:46,849 --> 00:56:49,518
<i>He's drawing the line again.</i>

667
00:56:54,899 --> 00:56:56,442
Why aren't you giving me one?

668
00:56:57,485 --> 00:56:59,195
What flavor is it?

669
00:57:11,290 --> 00:57:13,417
Are you crazy? We're at school!

670
00:57:14,877 --> 00:57:17,630
A pretty girl was gazing at me, asking me

671
00:57:18,547 --> 00:57:20,007
the flavor of my candy.

672
00:57:26,180 --> 00:57:28,391
I was only looking at your candy.

673
00:57:31,560 --> 00:57:33,270
-This?
-Yes, that.

674
00:57:36,065 --> 00:57:37,108
It tastes good, right?

675
00:57:38,275 --> 00:57:39,819
-Is it good?
-No.

676
00:57:39,902 --> 00:57:41,445
-It's not?
-No.

677
00:57:42,488 --> 00:57:45,574
There's something between them.
And my friend said

678
00:57:45,658 --> 00:57:49,203
she saw Jae-eon several times at the
convenience store near Na-bi's house.

679
00:57:49,286 --> 00:57:51,872
Come on. She lives near our school.

680
00:57:51,956 --> 00:57:53,916
He never goes to that convenience store.

681
00:57:54,959 --> 00:57:57,461
You know so much about Jae-eon, honey.

682
00:57:57,545 --> 00:57:59,088
Did you just call me "honey"?

683
00:57:59,171 --> 00:58:01,048
Come to think of it,

684
00:58:01,132 --> 00:58:03,843
they were giving each other looks
before they disappeared!

685
00:58:03,926 --> 00:58:05,636
Are they dating, then?

686
00:58:06,721 --> 00:58:08,472
Jae-eon doesn't date.

687
00:58:08,556 --> 00:58:10,683
Then are they just sleeping
with each other?

688
00:58:10,766 --> 00:58:12,977
You can gossip among yourselves later.

689
00:58:14,020 --> 00:58:16,814
We still have to discuss the venue
and budget of our workshop.

690
00:58:16,897 --> 00:58:19,150
Didn't we decide to finish this
in an hour?

691
00:58:19,233 --> 00:58:21,736
Come on, don't be so serious.

692
00:58:21,819 --> 00:58:23,195
It's all right.

693
00:58:23,279 --> 00:58:25,489
I guess he's in a hurry to go on a date.

694
00:58:26,115 --> 00:58:27,658
Let's finish up quickly.

695
00:58:32,121 --> 00:58:34,373
-Sorry I'm late.
-It's fine. Sit down.

696
00:58:36,083 --> 00:58:39,128
The professor wants us to check
the venue in person beforehand.

697
00:58:39,211 --> 00:58:41,130
We should go this weekend.

698
00:58:41,714 --> 00:58:43,466
Who can't make it?

699
00:58:48,179 --> 00:58:50,765
What? You can't make it, Jae-eon?

700
00:58:51,682 --> 00:58:52,767
No.

701
00:58:54,602 --> 00:58:55,644
Why?

702
00:59:02,151 --> 00:59:03,569
Hey, Na-bi!

703
00:59:04,111 --> 00:59:06,447
Why are you so dressed up today?

704
00:59:06,530 --> 00:59:08,491
-Is it okay?
-It looks great on you.

705
00:59:11,911 --> 00:59:13,370
Why weren't you at school?

706
00:59:13,454 --> 00:59:16,290
I was a little sick.
Don't you think I lost some weight?

707
00:59:16,874 --> 00:59:19,043
Yes, it looks like it. Are you okay now?

708
00:59:19,126 --> 00:59:21,921
I'm fine.
Right, and how was your birthday?

709
00:59:22,004 --> 00:59:23,547
Sorry I couldn't contact you.

710
00:59:23,631 --> 00:59:25,216
You don't need to be sorry.

711
00:59:25,758 --> 00:59:29,053
Did you talk to Sol?
She seemed pretty worried about you.

712
00:59:29,970 --> 00:59:33,140
The weather's really nice today.

713
00:59:33,724 --> 00:59:36,352
-It's totally spring, isn't it?
-It is.

714
00:59:38,187 --> 00:59:40,147
I don't want to work on assignments.

715
00:59:40,231 --> 00:59:42,608
Hey, Na-bi. You look so pretty.

716
00:59:42,691 --> 00:59:43,984
-Here to work?
-So pretty.

717
00:59:44,068 --> 00:59:46,612
-We're just having a short meeting.
-They're both pretty.

718
00:59:48,656 --> 00:59:49,740
Okay.

719
00:59:51,617 --> 00:59:52,660
Go on.

720
01:00:03,671 --> 01:00:05,714
What about me?

721
01:00:05,798 --> 01:00:07,424
It's been a while, Ji-wan.

722
01:00:07,508 --> 01:00:09,552
Why did you suddenly go off the grid?

723
01:00:09,635 --> 01:00:11,220
I was a bit sick.

724
01:00:13,430 --> 01:00:16,100
How does a fit girl like you
suddenly get sick?

725
01:00:16,684 --> 01:00:18,144
I know. Ji-wan is built like a brick.

726
01:00:18,227 --> 01:00:19,895
What were you sick with?

727
01:00:20,771 --> 01:00:24,066
Well, Jae-eon can't come
since he has plans.

728
01:00:24,150 --> 01:00:25,651
Anyone else who can't come?

729
01:00:26,694 --> 01:00:30,489
Na-bi. We're going to check the venue
for our workshop. Want to come?

730
01:00:31,407 --> 01:00:32,616
Well…

731
01:00:37,538 --> 01:00:39,415
I have plans.

732
01:00:40,332 --> 01:00:43,586
Right. If you have plans, I guess not.

733
01:01:00,269 --> 01:01:03,230
Na-bi and Jae-eon really seem
to be dating, right?

734
01:01:03,731 --> 01:01:05,774
I thought Na-bi had a crush on me.

735
01:01:06,483 --> 01:01:09,236
Are you still on about that?

736
01:01:10,237 --> 01:01:12,448
Do you guys want to go out for drinks?

737
01:01:12,531 --> 01:01:13,991
I have plans.

738
01:01:15,701 --> 01:01:17,620
Me too. I have plans, too.

739
01:01:30,257 --> 01:01:32,801
Jeez…

740
01:01:41,352 --> 01:01:42,478
What are you doing here?

741
01:01:42,561 --> 01:01:45,356
Na-bi. I'm really heartbroken.

742
01:01:45,439 --> 01:01:47,191
I know you're in a lot of pain after--

743
01:01:47,274 --> 01:01:48,734
What are you talking about?

744
01:01:51,654 --> 01:01:54,740
I heard the rumors. A lot of my students
attend your school.

745
01:01:54,823 --> 01:01:57,785
I keep hearing rumors about you,
even if I try not to.

746
01:01:57,868 --> 01:01:59,036
What do you mean?

747
01:02:00,162 --> 01:02:02,456
-What rumors?
-I heard you're seeing

748
01:02:03,165 --> 01:02:05,459
some jerk named Park Jae-eon or something.

749
01:02:06,210 --> 01:02:08,212
I heard he sleeps with everybody.

750
01:02:08,295 --> 01:02:10,798
I was so shocked when I heard
you were seeing him.

751
01:02:15,678 --> 01:02:18,222
I don't enjoy hearing that about my ex.

752
01:02:20,683 --> 01:02:21,767
Let go of me.

753
01:02:22,810 --> 01:02:25,187
You're giving me advice?
Who do you think you are?

754
01:02:25,271 --> 01:02:28,107
What? Then it's true?
You're seeing that jerk?

755
01:02:28,190 --> 01:02:30,067
Who are you to call him a jerk?

756
01:02:30,150 --> 01:02:31,694
-Yu Na-bi!
-What?

757
01:02:35,072 --> 01:02:37,324
You're not that kind of girl.

758
01:02:37,408 --> 01:02:41,745
You must've been lonely after we broke up.
But still, seeing a guy like that?

759
01:02:41,829 --> 01:02:43,330
Shut up and get lost.

760
01:02:50,254 --> 01:02:51,714
Hey, Na-bi…

761
01:02:54,550 --> 01:02:57,845
LAUNDRY

762
01:03:09,106 --> 01:03:11,150
That bastard.
Who is he to say such things?

763
01:03:35,090 --> 01:03:37,551
<i>I feel like I'm doing something wrong.</i>

764
01:03:39,261 --> 01:03:41,096
Don't you know any hot girls?

765
01:03:41,805 --> 01:03:44,058
Ask Jae-eon to introduce you.

766
01:03:45,142 --> 01:03:46,018
Park Jae-eon?

767
01:03:46,810 --> 01:03:49,229
To be honest,
we don't feel comfortable with him.

768
01:03:49,980 --> 01:03:52,566
Why? Did something happen?

769
01:03:52,649 --> 01:03:55,778
Don't you feel that he shows off
about being popular?

770
01:03:55,861 --> 01:03:58,238
When I asked him to introduce me
to a girl,

771
01:03:58,322 --> 01:04:02,034
he said something about feeling guilty
towards them. It totally pissed me off.

772
01:04:02,618 --> 01:04:05,454
Jae-eon really said that to you?

773
01:04:05,537 --> 01:04:07,164
He did.

774
01:04:07,247 --> 01:04:09,083
He's so rude just because he's popular.

775
01:04:09,166 --> 01:04:11,043
We don't think of him as a real friend.

776
01:04:11,126 --> 01:04:13,295
The others don't consider him
a friend, either.

777
01:04:13,379 --> 01:04:16,298
They just keep him close
since he's good-looking, that's all.

778
01:04:17,966 --> 01:04:19,593
His target is Na-bi these days.

779
01:04:20,260 --> 01:04:21,845
They seem to be getting close.

780
01:04:21,929 --> 01:04:23,430
I could totally tell.

781
01:04:24,056 --> 01:04:25,849
I did hear about that.

782
01:04:26,517 --> 01:04:28,310
So the rumors spread already.

783
01:04:28,394 --> 01:04:30,354
Jae-eon has nothing to lose.

784
01:04:30,437 --> 01:04:31,563
He must be so proud.

785
01:04:32,731 --> 01:04:35,984
I didn't think Na-bi would be like that.
She must be pretty open-minded…

786
01:04:36,735 --> 01:04:40,406
Open-minded?
That's just a nice way to put it.

787
01:04:41,115 --> 01:04:44,451
You really can't judge a book
by its cover.

788
01:04:45,369 --> 01:04:47,162
I should get going now.

789
01:04:47,746 --> 01:04:49,248
Okay. Let's go together.

790
01:04:54,503 --> 01:04:55,712
Yu Na-bi?

791
01:04:59,258 --> 01:05:00,926
Hello, Professor.

792
01:05:03,846 --> 01:05:05,097
Is this for the exhibit?

793
01:05:06,432 --> 01:05:08,976
Yes, I'm thinking of handing this one in.

794
01:05:17,568 --> 01:05:19,194
Is something troubling you?

795
01:05:19,278 --> 01:05:20,696
It's in pretty bad shape.

796
01:05:21,405 --> 01:05:22,739
<i>A right hook.</i>

797
01:05:24,199 --> 01:05:28,162
But still, if you focus well
and keep working on it,

798
01:05:28,996 --> 01:05:30,456
it could be a decent piece.

799
01:05:30,539 --> 01:05:33,083
All right. I'll work harder.

800
01:05:48,974 --> 01:05:53,479
People gossip about others

801
01:05:53,562 --> 01:05:55,814
and criticize others so easily.

802
01:05:55,898 --> 01:05:58,859
It's especially worse in Korea,
since it's a small country.

803
01:06:00,152 --> 01:06:03,614
That's why you should be careful
when you're young.

804
01:06:04,615 --> 01:06:07,993
You might think reckless behavior
can be forgiven because you're young.

805
01:06:11,163 --> 01:06:13,790
But from what I experienced,
it's not the case.

806
01:06:14,374 --> 01:06:15,584
There are consequences.

807
01:06:15,667 --> 01:06:18,837
You'll get hit with the aftermath
at a crucial moment later on.

808
01:06:18,921 --> 01:06:20,380
<i>A left hook.</i>

809
01:06:20,464 --> 01:06:23,217
No one will take responsibility
for your own life.

810
01:06:23,300 --> 01:06:26,845
So keep your head on straight.
You're graduating soon, you know.

811
01:06:26,929 --> 01:06:29,348
Everyone finds a job
before they graduate these days.

812
01:06:29,973 --> 01:06:31,683
<i>And an uppercut.</i>

813
01:06:32,518 --> 01:06:33,602
Right.

814
01:06:34,436 --> 01:06:35,854
I know how you feel,

815
01:06:35,938 --> 01:06:39,066
so I'm giving you advice since
I care about you. So keep that in mind.

816
01:06:39,900 --> 01:06:41,235
Yes, Professor.

817
01:06:41,944 --> 01:06:44,863
-Focus on your work.
-I will.

818
01:06:51,745 --> 01:06:52,955
<i>KO.</i>

819
01:07:06,301 --> 01:07:07,803
<i>It feels like</i>

820
01:07:07,886 --> 01:07:11,348
<i>the whole universe is telling me
to end it with Jae-eon.</i>

821
01:07:12,182 --> 01:07:13,350
Na-bi.

822
01:07:15,894 --> 01:07:19,022
Are you okay? You could've
fallen down on the trash.

823
01:07:19,898 --> 01:07:22,109
Yes, I'm fine.

824
01:07:22,901 --> 01:07:25,070
This is good timing.

825
01:07:25,153 --> 01:07:28,156
Could we meet for a moment later?
Just the two of us?

826
01:07:30,242 --> 01:07:32,661
Well, I like that you're asking first,

827
01:07:33,370 --> 01:07:36,123
but I'll be a bit tired
since I have lots of work today.

828
01:07:37,666 --> 01:07:40,252
What? I'm not talking about that.

829
01:07:42,546 --> 01:07:44,631
Let's talk.

830
01:07:45,757 --> 01:07:48,552
Okay. Will it be okay
to meet late at night?

831
01:07:48,635 --> 01:07:49,761
Yes, it's fine.

832
01:07:51,054 --> 01:07:52,514
I'll call you when I'm done.

833
01:07:54,016 --> 01:07:55,017
Okay.

834
01:08:06,737 --> 01:08:09,448
-Let's send it to the professor tomorrow.
-Okay.

835
01:08:09,531 --> 01:08:11,408
She won't read it until tomorrow anyway.

836
01:08:20,042 --> 01:08:21,627
-Aren't you leaving?
-What?

837
01:08:22,169 --> 01:08:27,049
Oh, well… I'm just going to finish
reading the paper I was looking at.

838
01:08:29,009 --> 01:08:30,052
Where is it?

839
01:08:30,135 --> 01:08:32,679
All right, then. I'll be off first.

840
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:35,182
Okay. Bye.

841
01:08:37,351 --> 01:08:41,188
I thought about it, and I guess
I must have lost it after breaking up.

842
01:08:41,271 --> 01:08:43,106
I don't know why I'm doing this

843
01:08:43,190 --> 01:08:45,108
with you.

844
01:08:48,445 --> 01:08:49,780
What do you mean?

845
01:08:52,366 --> 01:08:54,951
I want to focus on my work and school.

846
01:08:57,579 --> 01:08:59,456
This is an important time for me.

847
01:09:01,249 --> 01:09:03,168
I guess I'm talking too much, right?

848
01:09:03,877 --> 01:09:07,839
Yes. Aren't you going overboard?
We're not even going out.

849
01:09:12,344 --> 01:09:13,553
We should end it.

850
01:09:19,142 --> 01:09:21,353
Does this sound like I want to cut ties?

851
01:09:25,941 --> 01:09:28,568
But whatever I say,

852
01:09:28,652 --> 01:09:31,947
Jae-eon won't even blink an eye.

853
01:09:37,953 --> 01:09:41,790
<i>He's always so relaxed and calm,
but I'm always anxious.</i>

854
01:09:41,873 --> 01:09:45,335
<i>My ex cheated on me,
I got rejected by a guy who liked me,</i>

855
01:09:45,419 --> 01:09:47,963
<i>and rumors spread about me
being sex partners with the guy I like.</i>

856
01:09:50,549 --> 01:09:53,176
It sounds even worse like that.

857
01:10:02,018 --> 01:10:03,437
<i>We should end it.</i>

858
01:10:04,354 --> 01:10:05,939
<i>That's all I have to say.</i>

859
01:10:23,623 --> 01:10:24,916
Let's talk.

860
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:26,626
You have more to say?

861
01:10:28,253 --> 01:10:31,465
To be honest, I don't get
why you're so upset.

862
01:10:33,341 --> 01:10:35,427
You didn't need to ghost me like that.

863
01:10:39,556 --> 01:10:41,308
I said I'll see you at your house.

864
01:10:43,059 --> 01:10:45,312
I thought you'd take a long time.

865
01:10:46,480 --> 01:10:49,900
I thought I'd finish by 10 p.m.,
but it's taking longer than expected.

866
01:10:50,525 --> 01:10:51,526
Right.

867
01:10:53,320 --> 01:10:54,446
I see.

868
01:10:54,529 --> 01:10:58,074
<i>I ran thousands of simulations
inside my head…</i>

869
01:10:59,159 --> 01:11:00,577
You look pretty serious.

870
01:11:03,163 --> 01:11:04,623
What did you want to say?

871
01:11:04,706 --> 01:11:07,000
<i>But the moment I looked into his eyes,</i>

872
01:11:08,543 --> 01:11:10,629
<i>my mind went blank.</i>

873
01:11:10,712 --> 01:11:12,005
Well…

874
01:11:14,591 --> 01:11:16,885
My ex-boyfriend came to my house.

875
01:11:16,968 --> 01:11:19,721
He seemed to have heard rumors about us.

876
01:11:21,932 --> 01:11:23,809
He said I should just date him instead.

877
01:11:26,853 --> 01:11:28,021
What did you say?

878
01:11:29,022 --> 01:11:30,774
I told him not to talk nonsense.

879
01:11:32,025 --> 01:11:33,026
Really?

880
01:11:33,109 --> 01:11:36,071
<i>"Really?" Is that it?</i>

881
01:11:41,159 --> 01:11:42,828
Is that what you wanted to say?

882
01:11:47,791 --> 01:11:50,126
Is there someone else you're seeing?

883
01:11:50,210 --> 01:11:51,628
<i>What's wrong with me?</i>

884
01:11:52,128 --> 01:11:54,673
<i>Why am I asking this
when I was about to end everything?</i>

885
01:11:59,803 --> 01:12:00,887
No.

886
01:12:02,305 --> 01:12:03,223
Really?

887
01:12:19,072 --> 01:12:20,532
Excuse me.

888
01:12:21,116 --> 01:12:23,743
Are you Park Jae-eon, by any chance?

889
01:12:24,870 --> 01:12:26,204
Yes.

890
01:12:27,873 --> 01:12:29,249
So it's you.

891
01:12:32,294 --> 01:12:34,087
You bastard!

892
01:12:36,006 --> 01:12:37,883
Sir! What's wrong?

893
01:12:37,966 --> 01:12:40,010
-What are you doing?
-Move.

894
01:12:40,093 --> 01:12:41,511
-Wait!
-Move!

895
01:12:41,595 --> 01:12:44,180
-Why are you doing this?
-Get out of the way!

896
01:12:46,266 --> 01:12:47,225
Na-bi!

897
01:13:42,697 --> 01:13:46,743
<i>Park Jae-eon has never been mine.
But it feels like I've lost him.</i>

898
01:13:46,826 --> 01:13:49,496
<i>How could Na-bi date a guy like Jae-eon?</i>

899
01:13:49,579 --> 01:13:53,166
-My girlfriend?
-Call me. Even if it's nothing special.

900
01:13:53,249 --> 01:13:56,211
<i>My whole house is filled
with traces of Jae-eon.</i>

901
01:13:56,294 --> 01:13:57,128
<i>Jerk.</i>

902
01:13:57,837 --> 01:13:59,339
<i>I guess it worked.</i>

903
01:13:59,422 --> 01:14:01,007
<i>How long are you going to avoid me?</i>

904
01:14:01,091 --> 01:14:02,884
We didn't get to finish
what we were talking about.

905
01:14:02,968 --> 01:14:06,721
This is how we always make up.
As if nothing happened.

906
01:14:06,805 --> 01:14:08,515
I just picked it up, thinking of you.

907
01:14:08,598 --> 01:14:10,558
-A gift for me?
-Yes.

908
01:14:10,642 --> 01:14:12,352
I was jealous.
Good luck on your presentation.

909
01:14:12,435 --> 01:14:14,854
<i>Who would like to assist Yu Na-bi?</i>

910
01:14:14,938 --> 01:14:17,023
I thought it'd be fun. Seems interesting.

911
01:14:17,107 --> 01:14:18,984
<i>Hey, Seol-a. I'll be there right away.</i>

912
01:14:19,067 --> 01:14:21,361
<i>How can he not even call once?</i>

913
01:14:21,444 --> 01:14:22,904
<i>I miss him.</i>

914
01:14:23,446 --> 01:14:27,575
Subtitle translation by: Ju-young Park
